Let $a+b = x,$ and $ab = y.$</think>
\begin{align*}
    (a+b)^2 &= a^2+b^2+2ab\\
    x^2 &= a^2+b^2+2y
\end{align*}
\begin{align*}
    a^2+b^2 &= (a+b)^2 - 2ab\\
       &= x^2-2ab
\end{align*}


\begin{align*}
    a^3 + b^3 &= (a+b)(a^2 -ab + b^2)\\
            &= (a+b)((a^2+b^2)-ab)\\
            &= x((x^2-2ab)-ab)\\
            &= x(x^2-3ab)\\
    a^3 + b^3 &= x^3-3x^2y
\end{align*}

\begin{align*}
    a^4 + b^4 &= (a^2+b^2)^2 - 2(ab)^2 \\
       &= (x^2-2ab)^2-2(ab)^2
\end{align*}

\begin{align*}
    a^4 + b^4 &= x^4 - 4x^2y + 2y^2
\end{align*}



\begin{align*}
    0 &= (a^3+b^3)+(a^4+b^4)-4(a+b)-1\\
      &= (x^3 - 3x^2y) + (x^4-4x^2y+2y^2) - 4x - 1\\
      &= x^4 + x^3 - 7x^2y + 2y^2 - 4x - 1
\end{align*}


From before, $y=ab$ we get
\begin{align*}
    x^4 + abx^3 - 7(ab)x^2 + 2(ab)^2 - 4x - 1 &= 0\\
    \boxed{x^4 + x^3y - 7xy^2 + 2y^3 - 4x - 1 &= 0}
\end{align*}

<answer> $x^4 + x^3y - 7xy^2 + 2y^3 - 4x - 1 = 0$ </answer>

